cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper deals with online interactive recommender systems, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new approach to collaborative filtering that takes into account the dependencies among items, which is a common problem in recommendation systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, and cs.CL, in that order.
